times.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US states</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Attorney general</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">ChatGPT</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Consumer protection</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/13/multimedia/13biz-openai-investigation-clqk/13biz-openai-investigation-clqk-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Justin Sullivan/Getty Images</media:credit><media:description>“We take the concerns raised by state attorneys general seriously,” OpenAI, headed by Sam Altman, said in a statement on Saturday.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>U.S. Bars Foreigners From Using Anthropic’s Most Advanced A.I. Models</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/technology/anthropic-mythos-fable5-blocked.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/technology/anthropic-mythos-fable5-blocked.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/technology/anthropic-mythos-fable5-blocked.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The company said on Friday night that the federal government had ordered limits on its Mythos and Fable 5 A.I. systems, citing national security concerns.</description><dc:creator>Cade Metz and Dustin Volz</dc:creator><pubDate>Sat, 13 Jun 2026 02:26:06 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computer security</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberdefense</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Cyberwarfare</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Hacker (computer security)</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Commerce Department</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">US Politics</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Donald Trump</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/12/multimedia/12biz-anthropic-jbcp/12biz-anthropic-jbcp-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Nicolas Tucat/Agence France-Presse — Getty Images</media:credit><media:description>Anthropic’s Mythos A.I. model has raised worries that it could be used to attack computer networks.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>D.O.J. Seeks to Halt Pollution Lawsuit Against Elon Musk’s Data Center</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/climate/xai-musk-mississippi-grok-turbine-lawsuit-naacp.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/climate/xai-musk-mississippi-grok-turbine-lawsuit-naacp.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/16/climate/xai-musk-mississippi-grok-turbine-lawsuit-naacp.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>The department cited national security concerns, saying Elon Musk’s company had played a crucial role in the Iran war. It also argued it has the authority to stop environmental lawsuits brought by citizens.</description><dc:creator>Karen Zraick and Hiroko Tabuchi</dc:creator><pubDate>Tue, 16 Jun 2026 17:27:45 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Air pollution</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Lawsuits</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Civil Rights</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Minorities</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Clear Air Act</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Pollution</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Environment</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Data center</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Earthjustice</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">EPA</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Justice Department</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">NAACP</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Mississippi</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tennessee</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/16/multimedia/16cli-musk-doj-vjqt/16cli-musk-doj-vjqt-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Brad J. Vest for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>Construction at xAI’s power plant in Southaven, Miss., in February. The NAACP has sued the company over air pollution from generators there.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>What to Know About Planned Social Media Bans in Australia, the U.K. and Beyond</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/15/world/europe/social-media-bans-worldwide.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/15/world/europe/social-media-bans-worldwide.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/15/world/europe/social-media-bans-worldwide.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Britain said it would ban social media access for children under 16 starting in 2027, joining several other countries introducing similar measures.</description><dc:creator>Amelia Nierenberg</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 15 Jun 2026 11:19:17 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Social Media</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Children</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Regulation and Deregulation</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Parenting</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Motherhood</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Fatherhood</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Australia</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Britain</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/15/multimedia/15int-social-media-bans-wtk-HFO-top-qzwg/15int-social-media-bans-wtk-HFO-top-qzwg-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Katie Collins/Reuters</media:credit><media:description>Students in Wimbledon, London, during an interview this year about social media. Public opinion in many countries has coalesced around the idea that more must be done to protect children online.</media:description></media:content></item><item><title>What the SpaceX I.P.O. Means for OpenAI and Anthropic</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/technology/spacex-ipo-openai-anthropic.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/technology/spacex-ipo-openai-anthropic.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/technology/spacex-ipo-openai-anthropic.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Strong investor interest in SpaceX could be good news for the A.I. rivals, which have signaled that they, too, intend to go public this year.</description><dc:creator>Mike Isaac</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 18:53:33 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">IPO</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Artificial intelligence</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Stocks</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Bonds</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Anthropic</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">OpenAI</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SpaceX</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Uber</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/15/reader-center/altman-anthro/altman-anthro-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.png" medium="image"><media:credit>The New York Times</media:credit></media:content></item><item><title>SpaceX’s Unlikely Journey From Far-Out Idea to $2 Trillion Juggernaut</title><link>https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/technology/spacex-ipo-journey.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</link><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/technology/spacex-ipo-journey.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss</guid><atom:link rel="standout" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2026/06/12/technology/spacex-ipo-journey.html?partner=rss&amp;emc=rss" /><description>Elon Musk said he had initially given SpaceX less than a 10 percent chance of succeeding. His rocket company has come a long way.</description><dc:creator>Ryan Mac, Kenneth Chang and Kirsten Grind</dc:creator><pubDate>Fri, 12 Jun 2026 20:48:07 GMT</pubDate><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">SpaceX</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Elon Musk</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">IPO</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Private spaceflight</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Space</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Starlink</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Satellite</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Computers and the Internet</category><category domain="http://www.nytimes.com/namespaces/keywords/nyt_des">Tech Industry</category><media:content url="https://static01.nyt.com/images/2026/06/12/multimedia/12biz-spacex-improbable-ctfk/12biz-spacex-improbable-ctfk-videoSixteenByNineJumbo1600.jpg" medium="image"><media:credit>Andres Kudacki for The New York Times</media:credit><media:description>A SpaceX ad on the Nasdaq MarketSite tower in Times Square. The company, which Elon Musk founded in 2002, began trading on the stock market on Friday.</media:description></media:content></item></channel></rss>